Issue #1753 : toggle snapping by spacebar

The spacebar was used to activate the command widget otherwise.

If (Options -> Application Preferences -> Defaults -> " Toggle free snap
mode when SPACE BAR is pressed") is set, spacebar won't trigger activate
the command line (use Ctl-M,or Key_Colon ':' to activate the command
line).

If the option is not set, pressing spacebar would activate the command
widget.

As other application preferences, need to restart the application after
this option change.

Fillet: a quick fix for circle trimming

Circles by definition is a complete circle of 360 degrees.

To trim a circle, the circle is converted to an arc of 360 degrees and
trimmed.

pen/layer tree widget: not shown by default

These new widgets make the default app size too tall on smaller displays
(like 720p).

We may consider keeping them as tabs, instead individual dock widgets.

The end user can always enable them by Menu: Widgets -> Dock Widgets
